<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
	<id>96137</id>
	<title>uniform resizing of selected objects</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">Inkscape has a feature:</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">Transform / [x] Apply to each object separately</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="3">
			<sentence id="3.1">which allows for the uniform resizing of selected objects.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="4">
			<sentence id="4.1">Unfortunately, copy / paste from Draw, results in a bitmap 
and therefore distorted result.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="5">
			<sentence id="5.1">A BETTER solution MIGHT be to have a similar feature in
LibreOffice Draw (or, for that matter, Libre Office in general
available from ALL apps.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="6">
			<sentence id="6.1">Right now, the only option appears to be, copy from (example: Calc)
to Draw, Ctrl_Alt-V (GDI-Metafile) and then break, group (individually),
and then resize each object.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="7">
			<sentence id="7.1">VERY TIME CONSUMING when dealing with objects more than two or three.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="8">
			<sentence id="8.1">Would be VERY nice and VERY welcome to have this as an option.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="9">
			<sentence id="9.1">Thanx</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
</bug>
